TokenPay MVP Roadmap
Phase 1: Environment Setup & Stellar Fundamentals
-- Install Rust and Soroban CLI (cargo install soroban-cli)
--  Set up Stellar Futurenet testnet account and fund it via Friendbot
 -- Install Freighter wallet browser extension for Futurenet
 -- Learn basic Soroban concepts: Contracts, WASM, Ledger, and RPC
Phase 2: Core Payroll Smart Contract (Rust/Soroban)
--  Initialize Soroban project: soroban contract init -- payroll_contract
--  Implement PayrollContract with the following functions:
-- register_employer: Store employer address and KYC hash
-- add_employee: Map employee to employer with salary amount
-- run_payroll: Time-locked distribution logic
-- claim_payroll: Employee withdraws their share
-- pause_contract: Admin emergency stop
 -- Write unit tests using soroban_sdk::testutils
 -- Build WASM: soroban contract build
Phase 3: Contract Deployment & Interaction
 Deploy contract to Futurenet: soroban contract deploy
 Create CLI scripts or use soroban contract invoke to test flows
 Verify contract events for payroll runs and claims
Phase 4: Next.js Employer Dashboard (Web UI)
 Initialize Next.js app in /web directory
 Integrate Stellar SDK (@stellar/stellar-sdk) and Freighter API
 Build UI for:
Connecting wallet
Adding employees (calling add_employee)
Triggering payroll (calling run_payroll)
 Display transaction status and history from the blockchain
Phase 5: Integration & Polishing
 Connect UI to deployed Futurenet contract
 Add error handling and loading states
 Basic documentation and "How to Run" guide
 Test full flow: Employer adds employee → Runs payroll → Employee claims
